Package com.model.engine

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    GameGrid
    Used to create a 2D grid and add gameObjects to it
    GameLogger
    Handles the game logging The logfile is placed in the directory where the game is executed under a directory named "GAME_NAME"-logfiles
    GraphicObject
    Holds all functions which are used to populate the game grid Converts game objects to a rectangle
    Level
    Handles creation of game level taking in level name, level index and level grid and putting it in a 2D array
    LoadGame
    Holds all methods which load an initial game
    Movement
    Holds all functions related to movement
  • Enum Summary
    Enum Description
    GameObject
    Represents the objects in the game Each object assigned a symbol which is used to read maps
